{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Col|4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","chapter":4,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":1,"text":"Masters, deal with your slaves justly and fairly, since you know that you too have a Master in heaven.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":2,"text":"Devote yourselves to prayer; stay alert in it with thanksgiving.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":3,"text":"At the same time, pray also for us that God may open a door to us for the word, to speak the mystery of Christ, for which I am in chains,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":4,"text":"so that I may make it known as I should.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":5,"text":"Act wisely toward outsiders, making the most of the time.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":6,"text":"Let your speech always be gracious, seasoned with salt, so that you may know how you should answer each person.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":7,"text":"Tychicus, our dearly loved brother, faithful minister, and fellow servant in the Lord, will tell you all the news about me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":8,"text":"I have sent him to you for this very purpose, so that you may know how we are and so that he may encourage your hearts.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":9,"text":"He is coming with Onesimus, a faithful and dearly loved brother, who is one of you. They will tell you about everything here.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":10,"text":"Aristarchus, my fellow prisoner, sends you greetings, as does Mark, Barnabas’s cousin (concerning whom you have received instructions: if he comes to you, welcome him),","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":11,"text":"and so does Jesus who is called Justus. These alone of the circumcised are my coworkers for the kingdom of God, and they have been a comfort to me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":12,"text":"Epaphras, who is one of you, a servant of Christ Jesus, sends you greetings. He is always wrestling for you in his prayers, so that you can stand mature and fully assured in everything God wills.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":13,"text":"For I testify about him that he works hard for you, for those in Laodicea, and for those in Hierapolis.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":14,"text":"Luke, the dearly loved physician, and Demas send you greetings.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":15,"text":"Give my greetings to the brothers and sisters in Laodicea, and to Nympha and the church in her home.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":16,"text":"After this letter has been read at your gathering, have it read also in the church of the Laodiceans; and see that you also read the letter from Laodicea.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":17,"text":"And tell Archippus, “Pay attention to the ministry you have received in the Lord, so that you can accomplish it.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","bookOrder":50,"chapter":4,"verse":18,"text":"I, Paul, am writing this greeting with my own hand. Remember my chains. Grace be with you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Col","chapter":4,"paragraphStarts":[1,2,7,10,18],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":2,"text":"Speaking to God and Others"},{"beforeVerse":7,"text":"Final Greetings"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Masters, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Col 3:22","book":"Col","chapter":3,"verse":22,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" deal with your slaves justly and fairly, since you know that you too have a Master in heaven."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Col 3:22","book":"Col","chapter":3,"verse":22}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Devote yourselves "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 12:12","book":"Rom","chapter":12,"verse":12,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" to prayer; stay alert in it with thanksgiving. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 12:12","book":"Rom","chapter":12,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"At the same time, pray also for us that God may open a door "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 14:27","book":"Act","chapter":14,"verse":27,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 16:9","book":"1Co","chapter":16,"verse":9,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 2:12","book":"2Co","chapter":2,"verse":12,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" to us for the word, to speak the mystery of Christ, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 2:7","book":"1Co","chapter":2,"verse":7,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Eph 3:4","book":"Eph","chapter":3,"verse":4,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Eph 5:2","book":"Eph","chapter":5,"verse":2,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" for which I am in chains, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 27:2","book":"Act","chapter":27,"verse":2,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 28:16","book":"Act","chapter":28,"verse":16,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 28:30","book":"Act","chapter":28,"verse":30,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Eph 6:18–20","book":"Eph","chapter":6,"verse":18,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ac 14:27","book":"Act","chapter":14,"verse":27},{"label":"1Co 16:9","book":"1Co","chapter":16,"verse":9},{"label":"2Co 2:12","book":"2Co","chapter":2,"verse":12},{"label":"1Co 2:7","book":"1Co","chapter":2,"verse":7},{"label":"Eph 3:4","book":"Eph","chapter":3,"verse":4},{"label":"Eph 5:2","book":"Eph","chapter":5,"verse":2},{"label":"Ac 27:2","book":"Act","chapter":27,"verse":2},{"label":"Ac 28:16","book":"Act","chapter":28,"verse":16},{"label":"Ac 28:30","book":"Act","chapter":28,"verse":30},{"label":"Eph 6:18–20","book":"Eph","chapter":6,"verse":18}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"so that I may make it known as I should. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Act wisely toward outsiders, making the most of the time. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Eph 5:15–17","book":"Eph","chapter":5,"verse":15,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Eph 5:15–17","book":"Eph","chapter":5,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Let your speech always be gracious, seasoned with salt, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 9:50","book":"Mrk","chapter":9,"verse":50,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 14:34","book":"Luk","chapter":14,"verse":34,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" so that you may know how you should answer each person. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 3:15","book":"1Pe","chapter":3,"verse":15,"letter":"c"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 9:50","book":"Mrk","chapter":9,"verse":50},{"label":"Lk 14:34","book":"Luk","chapter":14,"verse":34},{"label":"1Pt 3:15","book":"1Pe","chapter":3,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Tychicus, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 20:4","book":"Act","chapter":20,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ti 3:12","book":"Tit","chapter":3,"verse":12,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" our dearly loved brother, faithful "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 23:19","book":"Num","chapter":23,"verse":19,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" minister, and fellow servant in the Lord, will tell you all the news about me. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ac 20:4","book":"Act","chapter":20,"verse":4},{"label":"Ti 3:12","book":"Tit","chapter":3,"verse":12},{"label":"Nm 23:19","book":"Num","chapter":23,"verse":19}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I have sent him to you for this very purpose, so that you may know how we are "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Other mss read that he may know how you are"},{"kind":"text","text":" and so that he may encourage "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 16:25","book":"Luk","chapter":16,"verse":25,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" your hearts. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Eph 6:21–22","book":"Eph","chapter":6,"verse":21,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Col 2:2","book":"Col","chapter":2,"verse":2,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 16:25","book":"Luk","chapter":16,"verse":25},{"label":"Eph 6:21–22","book":"Eph","chapter":6,"verse":21},{"label":"Col 2:2","book":"Col","chapter":2,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Other mss read that he may know how you are"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He is coming with Onesimus, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Phm 10","book":"Phm","chapter":1,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Phm 1:16","book":"Phm","chapter":1,"verse":16,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" a faithful and dearly loved brother, who is one of you. They will tell you about everything here."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Phm 10","book":"Phm","chapter":1,"verse":10},{"label":"Phm 1:16","book":"Phm","chapter":1,"verse":16}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Col:4:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Aristarchus, my fellow prisoner, sends you greetings, as does Mark, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Phm 24","book":"Phm","chapter":1,"verse":24,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" Barnabas’s "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 4:36","book":"Act","chapter":4,"verse":36,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" cousin (concerning whom you have received instructions: if he comes to you, welcome him), "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Phm 24","book":"Phm","chapter":1,"verse":24},{"label":"Ac 4:36","book":"Act","chapter":4,"verse"